
==French==

===Etymology===
From [[Verlan]] for "français".  

===Noun===
'''Céfran'''  (''plural:'' '''[[Céfrans]]''')

# Slang for a French person; ''esp.'' a white (Caucasian) French person, or a French person without recent foreign-born ancestors.  Occasional employed as as a slur amongst France's ethnic Arab population.
#:''They are all French, but one is Arab, one is Black, and one is Céfran''

